HEADWORD: Wellspring
<hw>Well"spring`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A fountain; a
spring; a source of continual supply.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Understanding is a <qex>wellspring</qex> of life unto him that
hath it; but the instruction of fools is folly.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. xvi.
22.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Well-willer</ent>⟦br⟧
